/*!
\page typecast_dec2bin DEC2BIN Convert Decimal to Binary String

<p>
Section: \ref sec_typecast "Type Conversion Functions"
\section USAGE
Converts an integer to a binary string.  The syntax for its
use is
\verbatim
   y = dec2bin(x,n)
\endverbatim
where <tt>x</tt> is the positive integer, and <tt>n</tt> is the number of
bits to use in the representation.  Alternately, if you leave
<tt>n</tt> unspecified, 
\verbatim
   y = dec2bin(x)
\endverbatim
the minimum number of bits needed to represent <tt>x</tt> are used.
If <tt>x</tt> is a vector, then the resulting <tt>y</tt> is a character
matrix.
\section Example
Here we convert some numbers to bits

\if FRAGMENT
frag_typecast_dec2bin_000.m
0
dec2bin(56)
dec2bin(1039456)
dec2bin([63,73,32],5)
\endif


